  {
    "eu_id": "EU-0004",
    "kind": "section_text_panel",
    "page": "newspaper_d7fe1132386670993aae3dabc6247bc9_1",
    "primary_id": "mineru_newspaper_d7fe1132386670993aae3dabc6247bc9_1_6",
    "source": "header_anchor",
    "member_count": 2,
    "elements": [
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_d7fe1132386670993aae3dabc6247bc9_1_6",
        "observed_type": "title",
        "canon_role": "section_header",
        "text": "Agenda and Notice of Public Meeting of the Oregon Advisory Committee",
        "bbox": [
          0.07215686274509804,
          0.31393939393939396,
          0.3333333333333333,
          0.34
        ],
        "order": 12
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_newspaper_d7fe1132386670993aae3dabc6247bc9_1_25",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "In a previous revision to this collection, a PSC limit of Chinook salmon was established for the pollock industry participants in an industry- developed contractual arrangement, called an incentive plan agreement (IPA) that establishes an incentive program to minimize bycatch at all levels of Chinook salmon abundance. NMFS issues transferable Chinook salmon PSC allocations to eligible entities representing the catcher/ processor sector, the mothership sector, inshore cooperatives, and CDQ groups. Transferable allocations provide the pollock fleet the flexibility to maximize the harvest of pollock while maintaining Chinook salmon bycatch at or below the PSC limit.",
        "bbox": [
          0.6509803921568628,
          0.3151515151515151,
          0.923921568627451,
          0.5606060606060606
        ],
        "order": 13
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "eu_id": "EU-0005",
    "kind": "section_text_panel",
    "page": "newspaper_d7fe1132386670993aae3dabc6247bc9_1",
